IRS990.Description: Higher Education: Funds used by Fort Hays State University for growth and development.

Activity2.Description: Scholarship Programs: Scholarships are awarded to qualified recipients via scholarship committee selection. Scholarships were awarded in the amount of $1,471,074 to students attending Fort Hays State University. The average scholarship amount awarded is approximately $500.00. Scholarships are awarded based on criteria established through donor gift instruments.

Activity3.Description: Student Loan Programs: Loan Expenses. Funds available to students to enable them to continue their education at Fort Hays State University. (4,617 dollars)

Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.Explanation: The collections are a reflection of the mission of Fort Hays State University (FHSU) and the FHSU Foundation. As a regional institution, the impact on students and our constituency is broad based. Yet, our approach is very comprehensive in the Arts, Sciences, Business and the Health fields. The collection is shown and displayed annually as educational tools.
Earnings on the endowment funds support the educational undertakings at Fort Hays State University (FHSU) through scholarships, departmental support and student loans.
Other liabilites consist of annuity contracts payable and miscellaneous liabilities.
